            <title>[HTTPCLIENT-2107] PoolingHttpClientConnectionManager unsafe volatile field access</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HTTPCLIENT-2107</link>
                <project id="12310360" key="HTTPCLIENT">HttpComponents HttpClient</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;PoolingHttpClientConnectionManager assumes subsequent volatile reads on validateAfterInactivity and defaultSocketConfig result in the same value, which can result n incorrect assumptions or even null pointer exceptions.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We should read a snapshot to a local variable, and reuse the local snapshot.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
